Feature Job Setting Analysis Report
Warehouse Jobs Statistics
The analysis is for the event data table: sf_event_data
The analysis period starts at 2022-03-21 23:59:55.799897854 and ends at 2022-04-18 23:59:55.799897854
The column used for the event timestamp is event_timestamp
The column used for the record creation date in sf_event_data is created_at

STATISTICS ON TIME BETWEEN sf_event_data RECORDS CREATIONS
- Average time is 180.16713693942486 s
- Median time is 180.0 s
- Lowest time is 128.0 s
- Largest time is 541.0 s
based on a total of 3354 unique record creation dates.

The BEST ESTIMATE FOR sf_event_data UPDATES FREQUENCY is every 180 s

The longer time between records creations are due to 5 MISSING UPDATES.

sf_event_data UPDATES TIME starts every 180 s at 2.004 s and ends at 55.356 s

WARNING:
1 JOB is found to have run LATE in relation with other jobs.

The late jobs are:
2022-04-12 12:36:55.355610378

WITHOUT THE LATE JOBS, sf_event_data updates ends every 180 s at 5.997 s

If you believe this won't repeat in the future, you can rerun the analysis by
setting the parameter exclude_late_jobs to True
Job Frequency Recommendation
The RECOMMENDED FEATURE JOB FREQUENCY is every 180 s at 61 s.
This includes a buffer of 5 s to allow for late jobs.

WARNING:
4 JOBS appear to have recorded late records from missing jobs.
To measure the IMPACT ON THE RECOMMENDATION, the optimal blind spot is computed with and without those jobs.
Those jobs are:

Feature Job Setting Recommendation

In SUMMARY, the recommended FEATUREJOB DEFAULT setting is:

blind_spot: 395

Backtest Result
For the feature job setting:
- Frequency = 180 s / Job time modulo frequency = 61 s / Blind spot = 395 s
The backtest found that new records would have failed to be processed on time by 1 feature job.
Summary
Key findings:
  • Based on the past records created from 2022-03-21 23:00:00 to 2022-04-18 23:00:00, the table is regularly updated every 3 min at 2.004 s within a 53.352 s interval. 5 job failures have been detected.
  • The features computation jobs are recommended to be scheduled after the table updates completion and be set every 3 min at 61 s.
  • Based on the analysis of the records latency, the blind_spot parameter used to determine the window of the features aggregation is recommended to be set at 395 s.
